WEBVTT

00:02:27.257 --> 00:02:30.187
and he said, "I needed you last night."

00:02:30.211 --> 00:02:32.599
(Laughter)

00:02:32.623 --> 00:02:34.927
(Applause)

00:02:36.363 --> 00:02:37.513
And I said, "I'm sorry,

00:02:37.537 --> 00:02:40.620
my powers as a poet
and philosopher only go so far.

00:02:40.644 --> 00:02:41.857
I'm not sure I can --"

00:02:41.881 --> 00:02:43.418
But before we knew it,

00:02:43.442 --> 00:02:46.872
we were into a conversation
about his marriage.

00:02:46.896 --> 00:02:48.569
Here he was in his uniform,

00:02:48.593 --> 00:02:50.061
and the interesting thing was,

00:02:50.085 --> 00:02:52.298
he was looking up and down
the row of officers

00:02:52.322 --> 00:02:55.351
to make sure his supervisor didn't see

00:02:55.375 --> 00:02:57.865
that we was having a real conversation.

00:02:59.228 --> 00:03:02.073
But all of us live
at this conversational frontier